headline: Why Lam Research (LRCX) Stock Is Up Today
summary: Shares of semiconductor equipment maker Lam Research (NASDAQ:LRCX) jumped 1.6% in the morning session after Morgan Stanley raised its price target on the stock to $158 from $137. The firm kept its "Equal Weight" rating on the shares. This decision came as the analyst firm increased its forecast for the Wafer Fab Equipment (WFE) market, which is the machinery used to create computer chips.
